    "Freeze the number first: the 97 is currently unfalsifiable, which for a measurement is the same as wrong. A model tuned on a corpus that may contain the exam will score brilliantly on the exam — memorization presents as mastery, and the tell is exactly what happened: the biggest jump the program ever recorded. Extraordinary scores demand extraordinary hygiene, and 'same source, same period, different teams, no registry' is how contamination happens everywhere it happens — nobody cheats; the pipelines just never met.\n\nRun it as a measurement incident. Quantify: exact and near-duplicate matching between golden set and tuning corpus — expect fuzzy overlap (the same resolved ticket reformatted three ways), which is why the check needs similarity detection, not just ID joins. Re-measure: the uncontaminated subset gives you a defensible interim number; a fresh sample from post-tuning tickets (016's discipline, re-run) gives you the real one. The honest result is probably still good — 037's bake-off showed genuine taxonomy gains — just not record-breaking; the correction is from 'miracle' to 'solid,' which is survivable today and reputation-ending later. Correct with 034's craft: everyone who saw the 97 gets the honest series before it anchors in a QBR deck, framed as the instrument improving.\n\nThen make recurrence impossible rather than discouraged: a held-out registry — eval items lineage-tagged at creation, excluded from every training pipeline by ID at the plumbing layer (057's identity indexing built this rail for privacy; contamination control rides it for free), and a standing contamination check gating any eval publication on any tuned model (045's row). Audit the blast radius honestly — the bake-off's verdict itself may have been flattered. And celebrate the data engineer publicly and specifically: 027 taught this org that the first person to say red determines whether there's ever a second — a culture where the pipeline-cleaner who un-discovered a miracle gets thanked is the only durable contamination control there is.",
