    "The eval program built across 016–045 worked — too well, in one dimension: the customer's monthly eval spend (judge-model calls, regression suites on every behavior PR, weekly production sampling, red-team automation, depth-indexed long-session traces) just crossed $210k — exceeding the $180k serving bill that triggered 038's crisis. Finance flags it with the obvious question: 'You spend more checking the AI than running it?' The eval team's answer — 'quality has a price' — is true and about to lose the budget fight. The suites also have real waste: full regression on typo-level prompt changes, judge calls re-scoring unchanged behaviors, nightly red-team runs that haven't found a new attack class in a month. Right-size it without gutting it.",
