    bottleneck: "The review system fights human nature and loses on schedule: when 99% of items are fine, sustained vigilance is psychologically impossible (automation bias isn't a character flaw — it's the documented response to reliable automation), and the gate's design — review everything, uniformly, forever — guarantees the decay while its telemetry (approval rate, review time) was never watched as the health metric it is; the oversight exists on paper exactly as 027's program existed on dashboards.",
