    nextMove: "Redesign for attention as the scarce resource it is: (1) triage what humans see — risk-scored routing (amount, vendor novelty, deviation from precedent, agent confidence) sends the routine 80% to sampled review and concentrates human attention on the genuinely reviewable 20% (010's ladder logic applied WITHIN the rung: earned autonomy for the boring classes); (2) measure review quality, not review throughput — seed the queue with known-bad drafts (canaries: synthetic errors of the classes that matter — wrong vendor, policy violation, 044's adversarial cases repurposed) and track catch rates per reviewer; a reviewer who misses canaries isn't reviewing, whatever their click count says; (3) make deep review structurally different from approval — the items routed to humans get a friction-appropriate interface (the diff against precedent highlighted, the risk factors named, an attestation that requires engaging with the specific flags — not a bare approve button); (4) close the loop on reviewer performance — catch rates and calibration feed back to reviewers (their own Gnomon), and chronic rubber-stamping routes to their manager as a capability gap, not a discipline case; (5) report the redesign to the audit committee in their language — 'oversight' redefined from 'a human clicked' to 'measured human catch-rate on seeded risks, concentrated where risk lives' — which is an answer that survives their follow-up.",
